# Everything Docker should NOT send into the build context. A smaller context
# means faster `docker build` and prevents stale/host-specific files from leaking
# into the image.

# Dependencies — reinstalled fresh inside the build (never copy host node_modules,
# which may be built for a different OS/arch).
**/node_modules

# Build output — the image's `build` stage compiles dist/ itself; copying a host
# dist/ would risk shipping stale code.
**/dist

# Version control & CI
.git
.github
.gitignore

# Local env & secrets — must NEVER enter an image.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Editor / OS noise
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store

# Tests, coverage, logs — not needed at runtime.
**/*.test.ts
**/coverage
**/*.log

# Docker files themselves
Dockerfile
.dockerignore

# Misc
README.md
*.md